DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260302
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260401
SUMMARY:A Taste of Rome
LOCATION:Café Q
DESCRIPTION:Category: Food & Beverage\nPrice: Free / Included\nStatus: Avai
 lable\nTime: 5 PM – 9 PM\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/ev
 ents/175068\n\nLet your palate wander to the Eternal City with our A Taste
  of Rome dinner experience\, celebrating the soulful\, time-honored flavor
 s of Italy’s capital. Available exclusively during dinner service\, this
  limited-time offering honors Rome’s culinary tradition—where simplici
 ty and exceptional ingredients take center stage.\n\nBegin with Bruschetta
  alla Romana\, bright with cherry tomato\, caper\, garlic confit\, and bas
 il on toasted ciabatta. Savor golden Gnocchi alla Romana in pomodoro with 
 Parmigiano Reggiano\, and the beloved Spaghetti alla Carbonara\, where gua
 nciale\, pecorino romano\, and egg yolk come together in perfect harmony. 
 For the main course\, Saltimbocca with Vignarola pairs tender veal\, prosc
 iutto di San Daniele\, sage\, and a vibrant spring vegetable ragù.\n\nEac
 h dish reflects Rome’s effortless balance of rustic authenticity and qui
 et refinement.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175068
CATEGORIES:Food & Beverage
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-176383@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T120000
SUMMARY:Hands-On Impact: Volunteer with Wonderfund
LOCATION:Offsite: Roadrunner
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Impact Fund\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 5 spo
 ts left\nStatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/ev
 ents/176383\n\nJoin The ’Quin Impact Fund for the fourth annual Period P
 arty\, hosted by The Wonderfund\, a hands-on volunteer experience bringing
  together women from across Greater Boston to create immediate\, tangible 
 impact for teens engaged with the Massachusetts Department of Children and
  Families.\n\nDuring this high-energy volunteer event\, more than 500 part
 icipants will come together to assemble 10\,000 menstrual hygiene kits\, e
 nsuring young people across the Commonwealth have reliable access to essen
 tial menstrual products. These kits will be distributed to all 29 DCF area
  offices\, where social workers can provide them directly to the teens the
 y support. Last year’s effort packed and distributed more than 13\,000 k
 its - be a part of helping to do it again. \n\n*This event is complimentar
 y and reserved for members only.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/176383
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Impact Fund
END:VEVENT
