BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175778@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T183000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: The Edge of Possible with Monet Izabeth 
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist Only\nEve
 nt URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175778\n\n5:00PM Reception
 \, 5:30PM Discussion \nAn evening of extraordinary endurance and perspect
 ive awaits with solo adventurer and storyteller Monet Izabeth. In January 
 2026\, she became the first American woman to ski solo and unsupported to 
 the South Pole\, traveling 700 miles across Antarctica over 57 days. Alone
  in whiteouts and subzero temperatures\, hauling every supply herself\, he
 r expedition was a profound test of resilience\, preparation\, and the dec
 ision to begin before feeling fully ready.\n\nBased between Massachusetts 
 and Nepal\, Monet has built her career designing immersive\, locally led j
 ourneys that connect travelers more deeply to place and people - while ins
 piring a global community to step beyond what feels comfortable and into w
 hat feels possible.\n\nThe conversation will be moderated by journalist Bi
 lly Baker\, who chronicled Monet’s journey\, offering insight into both 
 the public story\, the personal reality behind it and what we can all lear
 n from choosing the extraordinary. \n\n*This event is complimentary and r
 eserved for members only. Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175778
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
