BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-178464@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260402T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260402T130000
SUMMARY:Women\, Worth & Wisdom: Allyship
LOCATION:Bondo
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: $35.00 per person\nAvailability:
  32 spots left\nStatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse
 .com/events/178464\n\n11:30AM Lunch\, 12:00PM Discussion \n\nJoin us for 
 the third installment of our four-part series\, Women\, Worth & Wisdom\, l
 ed by Colette Phillips\, founder of Get Konnected. This ongoing conversati
 on brings together influential women from across industries to share persp
 ective\, lived experience\, and the enduring impact of women championing o
 ne another.\n\nIn this session\, Colette will be joined by Kathleen McQuig
 gan\, Partner and Portfolio Manager at Brown Advisory\, and Margaret McKen
 na\, President Emeritus of Lesley University\, for a wide-ranging dialogue
  on allyship - its nuances\, its necessity\, and its power to shape more i
 nclusive and equitable pathways forward.\n\nThoughtful\, engaging\, and in
 tentionally open in spirit\, the afternoon invites meaningful exchange and
  connection among peers.\n\n*This event is offered at $35 per person\, plu
 s tax\, to account for the buffet lunch\, enjoyed during the program. Rese
 rvations are open to members\, plus one guest. Cancellations made within 4
 8 hours of the event are subject to a full charge.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/178464
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-177698@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260402T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260402T190000
SUMMARY:Meet the Maker: Derek Baljeu of Knights Bridge Winery | Session I
LOCATION:The Muse
DESCRIPTION:Category: Food & Beverage\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist Only\n
 Event URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/177698\n\nSpend an enga
 ging evening with Derek Baljeu\, Winemaker at Knights Bridge Winery\, whos
 e thoughtful approach to winemaking blends scientific rigor with a deep re
 spect for the vineyard. A graduate of University of California\, Davis wit
 h both bachelor’s and master’s degrees in Viticulture and Enology\, De
 rek brings a dynamic perspective shaped by hands-on vineyard experience\, 
 academic research\, and a passion for exploring the evolving story each vi
 ntage tells.\n\nThis reception-style tasting offers an opportunity to min
 gle with fellow members and connect with Derek as he shares insights into 
 the philosophy and craft behind his wines—where terroir\, seasonality\, 
 and careful stewardship converge to create expressions that are both preci
 se and authentic.\n\nGuests will enjoy a curated tasting of Knights Bridge
  Pont de Chevalier Sauvignon Blanc and Knights Bridge Haggerty Road Red Bl
 end\, marking the Boston launch of Haggerty Road. Throughout the evening\,
  members are invited to explore the character of Knights Valley fruit and 
 the creative process that transforms grape to glass in a relaxed\, convers
 ational setting.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members 
 only. Light bites will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/177698
CATEGORIES:Food & Beverage
END:VEVENT
