BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-178419@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T130000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: A Focus on Men's Health
LOCATION:The Pub
DESCRIPTION:Category: Health & Wellness\nPrice: $35.00 per person\nAvailabi
 lity: 39 spots left\nStatus: You are Confirmed\nEvent URL: https://members
 .thequinhouse.com/events/178419\n\n11:30AM Lunch\, 12:00PM Discussion\nBio
 hacking\, sleep optimization\, performance psychology—today’s approach
  to men’s health goes far beyond the annual checkup. This forward-thinki
 ng conversation brings together Dr. Michael Goldstein\, lecturer at Harvar
 d Medical School and Director of Innovation at Cambridge Psychology Group\
 , alongside clinicians Dr. Jay Luthar\, Founder and Medical Director of Lu
 tanen Health & Faculty at Harvard Medical School\, and Dr. Thomas Hagan\, 
 Certified Chiropractic Sports physician with experience working with profe
 ssional athletes and the Boston Red Sox.\n\nTogether\, they will unpack th
 e science behind better sleep\, breathwork\, wearable health technology\, 
 and the behavioral shifts that help high performers sustain energy\, clari
 ty\, and longevity. Drawing from work with elite athletes and high-achievi
 ng professionals\, the panel will explore how data\, mindfulness\, and dai
 ly habits intersect to shape modern wellness.\n\n*This event is offered at
  $35 per person\, plus tax\, to account for the buffet lunch offered throu
 ghout the program. This event is reserved for members only. Cancellations 
 made within 48 hours of the event or failure to attend will result in a fu
 ll charge.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/178419
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
END:VEVENT
