DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T153000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: The Works of Yinka Shonibare
LOCATION:The Reading Room
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 44 spots left\nS
 tatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/17924
 4\n\n2:00PM Reception\, 2:30PM Discussion\nJoin The ’Quin House Art Cura
 tor Kate Chertavian in conversation with Trevor Smith\, Director of the Pr
 esent Tense Initiative at the Peabody Essex Museum\, for an engaging discu
 ssion on the work of British-Nigerian artist Yinka Shonibare whose works c
 urrently on view in The ’Quin’s Special Exhibition\, presented in The 
 Lobby and The Reading Room through April 6th.\n\nDrawing from a curatorial
  perspective\, the conversation will explore Shonibare’s distinctive pra
 ctice\, known for its use of Dutch wax fabric and reimaginings of art-hist
 orical imagery\, and its continued resonance in contemporary dialogues aro
 und cultural identity.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for me
 mbers\, plus one registered guest. Light bites and refreshments will be se
 rved.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/179244
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
