BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-178471@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T183000
SUMMARY:Author Talk: "The Best Dog in the World" with Alice Hoffman
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 26 spots left\nS
 tatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/17847
 1\n\n5:00PM Reception\, 5:30PM Discussion\nFor anyone who has ever loved a
  dog\, the bond needs little explanation. Join us for an intimate evening 
 with bestselling author Alice Hoffman\, whose work so often explores the d
 epths of love\, connection\, and what it means to care deeply—for one an
 other and for the animals who share our lives.\n\nDrawing from her new ess
 ay collection\, The Best Dog in the World: Essays on Love\, Hoffman refle
 cts on the joy\, loyalty\, and quiet wisdom our canine companions bring. F
 eaturing contributions from an extraordinary group of writers\, the collec
 tion is a heartfelt tribute to the dogs who leave lasting imprints on our 
 lives.\n\nThe conversation will be moderated by Mike Travis\, Chief Devel
 opment Officer of MSPCA-Angell\, one of the nation’s leading animal wel
 fare and veterinary care organizations. Founded in 1868\, MSPCA-Angell has
  long been at the forefront of animal protection and compassionate care—
 an institution with which Hoffman shares a personal connection\, having en
 trusted them with the care of her own dogs over the years.\n\nWarm\, thoug
 htful\, and deeply resonant\, this conversation offers a moving exploratio
 n of companionship\, empathy\, and the enduring bond between people and th
 eir animals.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members only
 . Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/178471
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
