BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-176384@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260326T084244Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260426
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260429
SUMMARY:Explorateur: Chef Arnaud Faye from Le Bristol Paris
LOCATION:Bondo
DESCRIPTION:Category: Food & Beverage\nPrice: Free / Included\nStatus: Avai
 lable\nTime: 5:30 PM – 10 PM\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.co
 m/events/176384\n\nThe globally inspired Explorateur culinary series welco
 mes Chef Arnaud Faye\, Executive Chef of the esteemed Le Bristol Paris and
  a recipient of the prestigious Meilleur Ouvrier de France distinction. At
  the helm of the Palace’s celebrated dining venues\, including the three
  Michelin star restaurant Epicure\, Chef Faye is widely recognized for a c
 uisine that marries classical French technique with contemporary refinemen
 t.\n\nFor his residency at The ‘Quin\, hosted in Bondo\, Chef Faye prese
 nts a bespoke menu inspired by the culinary philosophy that defines Epicur
 e. Guided by the rhythm of the seasons and the exceptional quality of ingr
 edients\, his cuisine reveals a remarkable balance of precision\, purity\,
  and restraint\, where each dish reflects a deep respect for French terroi
 r and the traditions that shape it.\n\nConceived as a rare invitation into
  one of Paris’s most storied kitchens\, this experience offers members a
 n intimate glimpse into Chef Faye’s world of modern French gastronomy. T
 hrough elegant compositions and refined flavors\, the spirit of Le Bristol
  Paris arrives in Boston for a limited time.\n\nMembers can look forward t
 o a menu shaped by seasonality\, precision\, and a deep respect for except
 ional ingredients and culinary tradition. Highlights may include oysters a
 ccented with citrus and kombucha\, lobster paired with butternut squash an
 d yuzu\, and A5 wagyu complemented by seasonal morels. Each course reflect
 s Chef Faye’s pursuit of balance and clarity of flavor\, offering a refi
 ned glimpse into the elegant\, ingredient driven cuisine that defines one 
 of Paris’s most celebrated kitchens.\n\nTo secure your place for this ra
 re culinary residency with Chef Arnaud Faye\, we invite you to reserve you
 r table using the link below.\n\n*The six-course dinner is priced at $350+
 + to be charged at the time of booking.  Please note that beverage is not
  included in the ticket price. The evening will feature a thoughtfully cur
 ated progression of courses\, including a special moment created exclusive
 ly for this residency. Due to advance preparations\, unavoidable cancellat
 ions that are made less than 72 hours prior to your reservation will not b
 e eligible for a refund. Reservations may be made through the Member Porta
 l. Members may invite up to three guests per seated member.\n\nMake a Rese
 rvation.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/176384
CATEGORIES:Food & Beverage
END:VEVENT
